original: Jonsson, Frans Oscar, folksikollära-re, rektor, Falköping, f. 2/6/95 i Agnetorp, Skarab. 1., av godsäg. Frans J. o. Klara Jonsdotter. G. 24 m. Edit Lindh. Barn: Inge f. 25, Berit 27, Berndt 30, Ulla-Kajsa 34. — Folksk:-lär:ex. i Linköp. 22. Folksk:lär. i Tibro 22-31 o. i Falköp. sed. 31, rektor v. Falköp. stads yrkessk. sed. 47. Ordf. i barnav :ndn sed. 39, v. ordf. i pens :ndn 42, led. av kyrkofullm. sed. 39, ordf. sed. 47, v. ordf. i S. Skarab.-krets, av SFF 40-46, diistr :chef f. Väs-tergötl scoutdistr. 36-41. Hoibby: bil-orientering. Sv. scoutunionens förtj :m. i guld.
translated: Jonsson, Frans Oscar, Elementary school teacher, Principal, Falköping, b. 2/6/95 in Agnetorp, Skaraborg County, the first child of Frans J. (a landowner) and Klara Jonsdotter. Married to Edit Lindh in 19xx. Children: Inge b. 25, Berit b. 27, Berndt b. 30, Ulla-Kajsa b. 34. Earned an elementary school teaching degree from Linköping in 1922. Worked as an elementary school teacher in Tibro from 1922 to 1931, and in Falköping since 1931. Became principal of the vocational school in Falköping in 1947. Served as chairman of the children's council from 1939, vice chairman of the pension council from 1942, member of the church council since 1939, chairman since 1947, vice chairman of the South Skaraborg district of the Swedish Women's Voluntary Defense Organization from 1940 to 1946, and district commissioner of the West Gothia Scout district from 1936 to 1941. Hobbies: Car-navigation. Awarded the Swedish Scout Union's merits in gold.
